The paper deals with coded caching in wireless multi-antenna communications, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a new scheme for selecting the level of subpacketization based on basic network parameters, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). The use of beamforming and caching also involves multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
